			<div class="row">
				<div class="grid-two-thirds float-center">
					<h2 class="text-center">Offsets</h2>

					<p>Push grids to the right by adding an <code>.offset-*</code> class. Center grids with the <code>.float-center</code> class. Obviously, the grids and offsets cannot add up more than a whole or they'll spill outside of the container.</p>

				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="grid-three-fourths offset-fourth"><div class="hero hero-condensed">.grid-three-fourths .offset-fourth</div></div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="grid-third"><div class="hero hero-condensed">.grid-third</div></div>
				<div class="grid-third offset-third"><div class="hero hero-condensed">.grid-third .offset-third</div></div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="grid-two-thirds float-center"><div class="hero hero-condensed">.grid-two-thirds .float-center</div></div>
			</div>

			<pre><code class="language-markup">&lt;div class="row"&gt;
